Thr Prior v. Henry T uylrt (pp. 150-8). Asslze of novel disseisin for a house in Cambridge The alleged disseisin consists in the tenant having blocked up a door· way so that his landlord‚ the Prior, cannot enter to distrain for rent arrear. The jurors find a verdict for the defendant, and he has judgment. However the Prior threatens an ‘attaint,' and the defendant yields. The record of the assize is given at length. An ‘attaint' was a proceeding in which the twelve jurors might be convicted of having swom falsely by a verdict of twenty-four other jurors, and the ‘attainted ’ jurors would be severely punished.
